Firefighters and emergency services personnel are currently battling a blaze at a building in Dr Pixley Ka Seme Street, formerly known as West Street in the Durban CBD. Emer-G-Med spokesperson, Kyle Van Reenen said at this stage he can confirm that 13 people have been evacuated and treated for injuries, ranging from minor to moderate, following a fire at a building in Dr Pixley Ka Seme Street, formerly known as West Street. “No children were found or injured. No fatalities were reported,” he said.